From d4b85059a857634b9c2200d4b1f02d24b1948218 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Justin Suess <utilityemal77@gmail.com>
Date: Mon, 29 Jun 2026 17:35:15 -0400
Subject: [PATCH 04/14] drm/sun4i: sun8i_hdmi_phy: add H616 and A523 HDMI PHY
 support

Add two new HDMI PHY variants to the sun8i dw-hdmi PHY driver:

  - sun50i-h616-hdmi-phy: same Innosilicon-family init sequence as the
    H6, only the mpll/curr/phy tuning tables differ.

  - sun55i-a523-hdmi-phy: the DW-HDMI controller reports a vendor PHY on
    this SoC, so it needs custom dw_hdmi_phy_ops rather than the DWC
    mpll_cfg path. Port the Inno PHY bring-up from the BSP, including the
    byte-addressed register file (val_bits=8) handled via a per-variant
    regmap_config and the prePLL/postPLL + drive tables.

phy_init becomes optional (variants with custom phy_ops do all bring-up
in ->init), and a per-variant regmap_config overrides the default.
---
